{
  "texts": [
    "In future work, we may perform experiments to evaluate the actual robustness of LLMs against sensor noise, by leveraging the real-world smart home data that we are currently collecting from the homes of elderly subjects in the context of a project in collaboration with neurologists.",
    "We may also design possible prompting strategies to make the LLM aware that the processed windows may be noisy.",
    "Conclusion and Future WorkIn this paper, we presented ADL-LLM: a zero-shot method for ADL recognition in smart-home environments.",
    "We showed that LLMs can reach recognition rates close to the ones of supervised approaches, with the benefit of not requiring labeled data.",
    "While we evaluated ADL-LLM on public datasets, we intend to investigate its effectiveness in the specific medical context of neurology, considering data from real subjects at risk of cognitive decline."
  ]
}